# perform association analysis with the transcriptome structure

ind$coord -> svd.o

as.data.frame(colData(vsd)[chosen,]) -> PhenoTypes.lv

identical (rownames(svd.o), rownames(PhenoTypes.lv))
## [1] TRUE
topPCA <- ifelse(ncol(svd.o) < 10, ncol(svd.o), 10)
svdPV.m <- matrix(nrow=topPCA,ncol=ncol(PhenoTypes.lv));

colnames(svdPV.m) <- colnames(PhenoTypes.lv);

for(c in 1:topPCA){
  for(f in 1:ncol(PhenoTypes.lv)){
    if(class(PhenoTypes.lv[,f])!="numeric") {
      svdPV.m[c,f] <- kruskal.test(svd.o[,c] ~ as.factor(PhenoTypes.lv[[f]]))$p.value
      } else {
        svdPV.m[c,f] <- summary(lm(svd.o[,c] ~ PhenoTypes.lv[[f]]))$coeff[2,4]
      }
  }
}

######################## Plot SVD Image #############################
myPalette <- c("darkred","red","orange","pink","white");

image(x=1:nrow(svdPV.m),
      y=1:ncol(svdPV.m),
      z=log10(svdPV.m),
      col=myPalette,
      breaks=breaks.v,
      xlab="",
      ylab="",

5.2 Enrichment analysis

A-) Biological Process (BP)

#Run functional enrichment analysis
enrichGo <- enrichGO(
  gene = chosen, # Set of genes to be analyzed
  universe = background, # Background representing the universe of genes
  OrgDb = org.Hs.eg.db, # Annotation database for human genes
  keyType = "ENSEMBL", # Type of identifier
  ont = "BP", # Biological Process - you can use MF or CC
  minGSSize = 10, # Minimum gene set size
  maxGSSize = 500, # Maximum gene set size
  pAdjustMethod = "BH", # p-value adjustment method
  pvalueCutoff = 0.05 # Significance threshold
)
#Visualizing the results
enrich_terms <- enrichGo@result
print(head(enrichGo))
